{l s='The right to be anonymous in not a explicit right for subjects as stated by the GDPR, but rather Privacy by Design.'  mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='Pseudonymization is the separation of data from direct identifiers so that linkage to an identity is not possible without additional information that is held separately.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='Inform people about the right to be anonymous. If a subjects wants to they can, for example, change their first and / or last name so they can not be directly identified.'  mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='This way, they will also still have an account they can log in to at a later point in time, keep the orders they placed and have the ability to change their info again if they want to.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='Important! Also inform your users that if they change their address credentials, it might cause a problem for future orders they place.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
